WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:25.650 --> 00:00:28.319 position:50% align:center
[SEENO EVIL laughs]

00:00:28.403 --> 00:00:31.281 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:00:31.364 --> 00:00:34.492 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:00:36.828 --> 00:00:38.538 position:50% align:center
[AI]
These aren't Seeno Evils!

00:00:38.621 --> 00:00:39.581 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
They're Haters.

00:00:39.664 --> 00:00:40.665 position:50% align:center
You've done too much

00:00:40.749 --> 00:00:42.792 position:50% align:center
to make yourself
stand out in this world.

00:00:44.586 --> 00:00:45.503 position:50% align:center
[AI grunts]
This way!

00:00:45.587 --> 00:00:47.130 position:50% align:center
What are Haters?

00:00:48.006 --> 00:00:49.799 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] Beings created
from the Seeno Evils

00:00:49.883 --> 00:00:54.012 position:50% align:center
from feelings of envy and spite
towards you and the other girls.

00:00:54.095 --> 00:00:55.930 position:50% align:center
They don't have the guts to show
their faces,

00:00:56.014 --> 00:00:59.059 position:50% align:center
but they're driven by madness
and stronger in groups.

00:00:59.142 --> 00:01:01.227 position:50% align:center
Maybe as strong as a boss.

00:01:01.311 --> 00:01:05.190 position:50% align:center
Your only choice is
to run or hide.

00:01:05.273 --> 00:01:08.234 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] They're after you:
the "heroes" in the limelight.

00:01:08.318 --> 00:01:10.153 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Are we heroes?

00:01:13.782 --> 00:01:15.492 position:50% align:center
Is your cut okay?

00:01:18.078 --> 00:01:19.871 position:50% align:center
There.

00:01:19.954 --> 00:01:22.457 position:50% align:center
What's your name?

00:01:22.540 --> 00:01:24.125 position:50% align:center
Yae Yoshida.

00:01:24.209 --> 00:01:25.919 position:50% align:center
Nice to meet you.

00:01:26.002 --> 00:01:28.755 position:50% align:center
We can just hide out in
here until the bell rings.

00:01:28.838 --> 00:01:29.839 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
You can't clear the mission

00:01:29.923 --> 00:01:32.967 position:50% align:center
if you choose not to fight.

00:01:33.051 --> 00:01:35.512 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] Well, focus on
maintaining the status quo

00:01:35.595 --> 00:01:38.390 position:50% align:center
for today. I have
a solution in mind.

00:01:38.473 --> 00:01:40.517 position:50% align:center
But! Yae's gotten injured.

00:01:40.600 --> 00:01:41.434 position:50% align:center
It's my fault she--

00:01:41.518 --> 00:01:42.644 position:50% align:center
Not a problem.

00:01:42.727 --> 00:01:44.688 position:50% align:center
She'll regenerate in
as little as ten minutes

00:01:44.771 --> 00:01:47.816 position:50% align:center
while she's inside her Egg.

00:01:47.899 --> 00:01:50.110 position:50% align:center
Dammit, they found us already?

00:01:50.193 --> 00:01:52.612 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] Protect the Egg
girl until time runs out.

00:01:52.696 --> 00:01:54.322 position:50% align:center
That's your top priority.

00:01:54.406 --> 00:01:57.492 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] Society is built on
"report, contact, consult."

00:01:57.575 --> 00:01:59.244 position:50% align:center
Say it out loud and share it.

00:01:59.327 --> 00:02:01.746 position:50% align:center
Right, our number
one objective is...

00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:02.997 position:50% align:center
[RIKA]
...Wonder...

00:02:03.081 --> 00:02:04.958 position:50% align:center
[MOMOE]
...Egg...

00:02:05.041 --> 00:02:06.626 position:50% align:center
[AI]
...Priority.

00:03:43.682 --> 00:03:44.766 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
Morning!

00:03:44.849 --> 00:03:47.602 position:50% align:center
Come on,
it's time for breakfast.

00:03:48.144 --> 00:03:49.854 position:50% align:center
Mom, I didn't sleep very well.

00:03:49.938 --> 00:03:50.814 position:50% align:center
Tough luck.

00:03:50.897 --> 00:03:52.816 position:50% align:center
Get up and help me out.

00:03:52.899 --> 00:03:54.943 position:50% align:center
Okay, fine.

00:04:02.492 --> 00:04:03.785 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
Ai!

00:04:05.286 --> 00:04:07.747 position:50% align:center
--Ai!
--What? I'm up!

00:04:13.294 --> 00:04:15.088 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
You want another one?

00:04:15.171 --> 00:04:16.589 position:50% align:center
--[AI] Sure.
--There.

00:04:16.673 --> 00:04:18.758 position:50% align:center
And also, I made you
omelet rice for lunch,

00:04:18.842 --> 00:04:20.385 position:50% align:center
since I know how you like it.

00:04:20.468 --> 00:04:22.804 position:50% align:center
[AI]
You did? Awesome.

00:04:22.887 --> 00:04:27.100 position:50% align:center
I think I'll make us
sukiyaki for dinner.

00:04:27.183 --> 00:04:28.643 position:50% align:center
What's the catch?

00:04:28.727 --> 00:04:29.894 position:50% align:center
What do you mean?

00:04:29.978 --> 00:04:32.105 position:50% align:center
You love sukiyaki, don't you?

00:04:32.188 --> 00:04:34.858 position:50% align:center
You only make it
on special days.

00:04:34.941 --> 00:04:39.904 position:50% align:center
Do I really? I guess so.

00:04:41.406 --> 00:04:43.074 position:50% align:center
Hey, Ai.

00:04:43.158 --> 00:04:47.037 position:50% align:center
With Mister Sawaki, try
to have a proper talk, okay?

00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:49.205 position:50% align:center
I know he's really
concerned about you,

00:04:49.289 --> 00:04:50.832 position:50% align:center
so would you consider it?

00:04:50.915 --> 00:04:52.500 position:50% align:center
I just want you
to think about the future

00:04:52.584 --> 00:04:54.753 position:50% align:center
a little bit more, you know?

00:04:56.880 --> 00:05:00.133 position:50% align:center
Sound good?

00:05:00.216 --> 00:05:02.344 position:50% align:center
Yeah, maybe.

00:05:02.427 --> 00:05:03.887 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
Ai.

00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:05.680 position:50% align:center
I said maybe!

00:05:05.764 --> 00:05:06.973 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
Okay.

00:05:25.575 --> 00:05:27.118 position:50% align:center
[MOMOE]
You went to school like that?

00:05:27.202 --> 00:05:29.996 position:50% align:center
[RIKA] Yup. Glistening lips
and eyes like a panda.

00:05:30.080 --> 00:05:31.122 position:50% align:center
[MOMOE]
A panda?

00:05:31.206 --> 00:05:32.457 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
She's here.

00:05:32.540 --> 00:05:33.541 position:50% align:center
Ai?

00:05:33.625 --> 00:05:36.503 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
But she's...

00:05:36.586 --> 00:05:38.630 position:50% align:center
She's skipping.

00:05:38.713 --> 00:05:39.923 position:50% align:center
That's weird.

00:05:40.006 --> 00:05:41.341 position:50% align:center
What's that about?

00:05:41.424 --> 00:05:43.259 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
Now she's kicking things.

00:05:43.343 --> 00:05:44.844 position:50% align:center
[RIKA, MOMOE]
Huh?

00:05:47.222 --> 00:05:49.015 position:50% align:center
What's going on?

00:05:49.099 --> 00:05:50.058 position:50% align:center
I don't know.

00:05:50.141 --> 00:05:52.394 position:50% align:center
Maybe something happened.

00:05:52.477 --> 00:05:55.021 position:50% align:center
[MOMOE] I had a nightmare
that started like this.

00:05:56.690 --> 00:05:58.566 position:50% align:center
It ended horribly.

00:05:59.859 --> 00:06:02.195 position:50% align:center
[RIKA]
Let's just watch for a bit.

00:06:06.449 --> 00:06:07.450 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Congratulations.

00:06:07.534 --> 00:06:09.577 position:50% align:center
I see you managed to escape.

00:06:09.661 --> 00:06:12.247 position:50% align:center
Yeah, but, like, what's
with those Haters, man?

00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:13.957 position:50% align:center
And who said we were heroes?

00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:17.127 position:50% align:center
It's not like we're doing all
this stuff for fun, you know.

00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:20.130 position:50% align:center
That may be, but they
can't be reasoned with.

00:06:20.213 --> 00:06:21.881 position:50% align:center
Those who stand out pay for it,

00:06:21.965 --> 00:06:24.300 position:50% align:center
in any time and any world.

00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:26.553 position:50% align:center
Didn't you
"have a solution in mind"?

00:06:26.636 --> 00:06:27.637 position:50% align:center
Let's hear it then.

00:06:27.721 --> 00:06:30.765 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Yes. Ah, it's arriving now.

00:06:30.849 --> 00:06:32.684 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
Thanks for waiting!

00:06:34.019 --> 00:06:35.353 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Within that case,

00:06:35.437 --> 00:06:37.981 position:50% align:center
you'll find little somethings
to support each of you.

00:06:38.064 --> 00:06:39.733 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA] Basically,
it's like what you call

00:06:39.816 --> 00:06:41.943 position:50% align:center
a "power up"
in your video games.

00:06:42.027 --> 00:06:43.153 position:50% align:center
Power up?

00:06:43.236 --> 00:06:44.946 position:50% align:center
[RIKA]
Beats me.

00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:47.741 position:50% align:center
Maybe it's a limited
use kind of thing?

00:06:47.824 --> 00:06:49.242 position:50% align:center
If you've had something
that handy all this time,

00:06:49.325 --> 00:06:51.036 position:50% align:center
why did you keep it from us?

00:06:51.119 --> 00:06:53.079 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
These are extremely valuable.

00:06:53.163 --> 00:06:55.498 position:50% align:center
We couldn't risk
you losing them.

00:06:55.582 --> 00:06:56.583 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
In other words,

00:06:56.666 --> 00:06:59.085 position:50% align:center
"Better not get
used to 'em, dummies."

00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:10.138 position:50% align:center
They're super cute!

00:07:10.221 --> 00:07:11.848 position:50% align:center
They're yours, free of charge.

00:07:11.931 --> 00:07:13.558 position:50% align:center
That said, one each.

00:07:13.641 --> 00:07:14.976 position:50% align:center
No hogging.

00:07:16.186 --> 00:07:17.604 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Pendants?

00:07:17.687 --> 00:07:19.356 position:50% align:center
[MOMOE]
They're pomanders, right?

00:07:19.439 --> 00:07:21.024 position:50% align:center
[RIKA]
Wow.

00:07:21.107 --> 00:07:23.485 position:50% align:center
So, how do we use these things?

00:07:23.568 --> 00:07:25.945 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] First, you have
to hatch them in this world.

00:07:26.029 --> 00:07:27.405 position:50% align:center
[MOMOE]
Hatch them?

00:07:27.489 --> 00:07:29.032 position:50% align:center
It's not as hard as it sounds.

00:07:29.115 --> 00:07:30.617 position:50% align:center
They respond to body heat,

00:07:30.700 --> 00:07:33.870 position:50% align:center
so just clasp them in
both hands and gently rub them.

00:07:34.496 --> 00:07:36.039 position:50% align:center
Oh, but don't do it here.

00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:39.626 position:50% align:center
Take them home, and wait to
open them until you're alone.

00:07:39.709 --> 00:07:41.044 position:50% align:center
Why, though?

00:07:41.127 --> 00:07:42.545 position:50% align:center
They require imprinting.

00:07:42.629 --> 00:07:46.508 position:50% align:center
They see whoever meets their
gaze first as their parent.

00:07:46.591 --> 00:07:49.344 position:50% align:center
Chant " <i>veni</i> ," and it will
call them from their eggs.

00:07:49.427 --> 00:07:51.096 position:50% align:center
" <i>Redi</i> " will return them.

00:07:51.179 --> 00:07:52.806 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
Latin?

00:07:52.889 --> 00:07:56.184 position:50% align:center
[RIKA]
I hope my baby's a hottie.

00:07:56.267 --> 00:07:58.895 position:50% align:center
Hey, what types do you
think are in them?

00:07:58.978 --> 00:08:01.606 position:50% align:center
We haven't imprinted yet,
so we can still trade, right?

00:08:01.690 --> 00:08:04.150 position:50% align:center
Neiru, you wanna
swap with me, maybe?

00:08:04.234 --> 00:08:05.235 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
No.

00:08:06.778 --> 00:08:08.863 position:50% align:center
Well, then I hope you
get the ugliest helper.

00:08:08.947 --> 00:08:10.824 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:08:15.078 --> 00:08:16.663 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
Ai.

00:08:18.373 --> 00:08:20.625 position:50% align:center
Is something wrong?

00:08:21.668 --> 00:08:23.628 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
You seem off today.

00:08:26.381 --> 00:08:28.299 position:50% align:center
It's kind of a long story.

00:08:36.683 --> 00:08:38.518 position:50% align:center
Heading home for the day, ma'am.

00:08:38.601 --> 00:08:39.894 position:50% align:center
Fine.

00:08:48.737 --> 00:08:50.071 position:50% align:center
[ALL 4]
<i>Veni.</i>

00:08:58.580 --> 00:08:59.914 position:50% align:center
A snake.

00:09:01.124 --> 00:09:02.625 position:50% align:center
Hey, buddy.

00:09:07.339 --> 00:09:09.424 position:50% align:center
I'm not quite sure how to react.

00:09:13.928 --> 00:09:15.180 position:50% align:center
Again?

00:09:15.263 --> 00:09:16.222 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Don't worry.

00:09:16.306 --> 00:09:18.767 position:50% align:center
We've got backup this time.

00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:20.226 position:50% align:center
<i>Veni.</i>

00:09:27.984 --> 00:09:29.361 position:50% align:center
Whoa, he ate it!

00:09:29.444 --> 00:09:31.446 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] Yes, Haters are
their favorite food.

00:09:31.529 --> 00:09:32.781 position:50% align:center
Envy and spite are essentially

00:09:32.864 --> 00:09:35.784 position:50% align:center
a helper's bread and butter.

00:09:36.576 --> 00:09:38.495 position:50% align:center
Right. Well, enjoy!

00:09:43.416 --> 00:09:46.336 position:50% align:center
That should solve
our Hater problem.

00:09:46.419 --> 00:09:47.837 position:50% align:center
What's wrong?

00:09:52.467 --> 00:09:55.470 position:50% align:center
Hey, Yae?
Why did you commit suicide?

00:09:57.180 --> 00:09:58.515 position:50% align:center
[YAE]
I can see.

00:09:58.598 --> 00:10:00.433 position:50% align:center
See what?

00:10:00.517 --> 00:10:03.603 position:50% align:center
[YAE]
Dead people, strong grudges.

00:10:04.229 --> 00:10:06.481 position:50% align:center
Whoa, like that kid
in<i>The Sixth Sense</i> ?

00:10:06.564 --> 00:10:09.150 position:50% align:center
[YAE]
No one ever believes me,
they just make jokes!

00:10:09.234 --> 00:10:10.610 position:50% align:center
There are incredibly
scary things out there

00:10:10.694 --> 00:10:14.197 position:50% align:center
that only I can see.

00:10:14.280 --> 00:10:18.159 position:50% align:center
Sorry. I don't
think I understand.

00:10:18.243 --> 00:10:19.577 position:50% align:center
[YAE]
It's fine.

00:10:19.661 --> 00:10:22.372 position:50% align:center
My friends ditched me
because it creeped them out.

00:10:22.455 --> 00:10:24.624 position:50% align:center
My parents and teachers
wouldn't believe me.

00:10:24.708 --> 00:10:29.129 position:50% align:center
In fact, they thought I was
crazy and put me in a hospital.

00:10:29.212 --> 00:10:32.173 position:50% align:center
But what really scared me
was what came next.

00:10:32.257 --> 00:10:33.967 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:10:34.050 --> 00:10:35.468 position:50% align:center
[YAE]
That hospital was overflowing

00:10:35.552 --> 00:10:37.429 position:50% align:center
with all these people's
anger and resentment.

00:10:37.512 --> 00:10:39.264 position:50% align:center
It was way worse
than the ghosts.

00:10:39.347 --> 00:10:40.557 position:50% align:center
So much scarier.

00:10:40.640 --> 00:10:41.850 position:50% align:center
Those people's voices.

00:10:41.933 --> 00:10:45.562 position:50% align:center
And their terrifying faces
poured into my head

00:10:45.645 --> 00:10:48.231 position:50% align:center
day in and day out!

00:10:48.314 --> 00:10:49.733 position:50% align:center
Calm down!

00:10:49.816 --> 00:10:52.694 position:50% align:center
Listen, a boss is coming,
but I'm gonna be ready for it.

00:10:52.777 --> 00:10:54.237 position:50% align:center
It's here!

00:11:11.004 --> 00:11:13.298 position:50% align:center
Ohto! Good evening.

00:11:13.381 --> 00:11:16.426 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Uh, uh... Uh...

00:11:16.509 --> 00:11:18.553 position:50% align:center
Good evening, sir.

00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:22.015 position:50% align:center
It's dinner time, so hurry
up and go dry your hair.

00:11:22.098 --> 00:11:23.475 position:50% align:center
Oh, here, I'll come help you.

00:11:23.558 --> 00:11:25.935 position:50% align:center
No, no, no.
I'm fine, you're our guest!

00:11:26.019 --> 00:11:27.896 position:50% align:center
Just make yourself at home.

00:11:29.314 --> 00:11:30.398 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:11:30.482 --> 00:11:31.900 position:50% align:center
He's staying?

00:11:37.447 --> 00:11:38.198 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
Here you go.

00:11:38.281 --> 00:11:39.741 position:50% align:center
[SAWAKI]
Thank you so much.

00:11:42.118 --> 00:11:44.537 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Thanks for dinner.

00:11:44.621 --> 00:11:46.831 position:50% align:center
Ai, hang on, don't go just yet.

00:11:46.915 --> 00:11:48.500 position:50% align:center
Young lady!

00:11:48.583 --> 00:11:52.045 position:50% align:center
We have something we
need to talk to you about.

00:11:52.128 --> 00:11:53.713 position:50% align:center
[AI] If it's about me
going back to school--

00:11:53.797 --> 00:11:55.173 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
It's not about school.

00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:57.175 position:50% align:center
So sit back down.

00:12:07.310 --> 00:12:08.978 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
Please just listen to us.

00:12:12.065 --> 00:12:16.319 position:50% align:center
We've been thinking that
we might like to start dating.

00:12:24.369 --> 00:12:25.912 position:50% align:center
Of course, we're not
going to move forward

00:12:25.995 --> 00:12:29.416 position:50% align:center
with that unless
you're okay with it.

00:12:42.846 --> 00:12:45.056 position:50% align:center
Whoa, my uncle and Ai's mom?

00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:46.307 position:50% align:center
Awesome!

00:12:46.391 --> 00:12:47.726 position:50% align:center
That means the two of us
might literally end up

00:12:47.809 --> 00:12:50.145 position:50% align:center
being family someday!

00:12:50.228 --> 00:12:52.313 position:50% align:center
What are you so excited for?

00:12:52.397 --> 00:12:53.857 position:50% align:center
'Cause it's good news.

00:12:53.940 --> 00:12:56.192 position:50% align:center
Right, Ai?

00:12:56.276 --> 00:12:58.862 position:50% align:center
Uh, that's not a
"good news" face.

00:12:58.945 --> 00:13:01.865 position:50% align:center
[MOMOE]
Are you against it?

00:13:01.948 --> 00:13:03.366 position:50% align:center
I said, "Do whatever.

00:13:03.450 --> 00:13:05.201 position:50% align:center
It's really none
of my business."

00:13:05.285 --> 00:13:07.620 position:50% align:center
So, you fought it
as hard as you could.

00:13:07.704 --> 00:13:09.497 position:50% align:center
I said, "But I won't
take care of you

00:13:09.581 --> 00:13:11.875 position:50% align:center
when you're old
or live with you."

00:13:11.958 --> 00:13:13.126 position:50% align:center
I told them
I'd put them in a home

00:13:13.209 --> 00:13:15.670 position:50% align:center
and only visit occasionally.

00:13:15.754 --> 00:13:16.796 position:50% align:center
Dang, nice work!

00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:18.214 position:50% align:center
You let 'em have it!

00:13:18.298 --> 00:13:19.215 position:50% align:center
But why?

00:13:19.299 --> 00:13:21.926 position:50% align:center
Do you feel bad
for your real dad?

00:13:22.010 --> 00:13:22.802 position:50% align:center
[AI]
No.

00:13:22.886 --> 00:13:24.054 position:50% align:center
They're already divorced,

00:13:24.137 --> 00:13:26.598 position:50% align:center
and I think my Dad is
also dating someone new.

00:13:26.681 --> 00:13:28.683 position:50% align:center
Then, I don't
understand the problem.

00:13:28.767 --> 00:13:30.393 position:50% align:center
Seriously?

00:13:30.477 --> 00:13:31.561 position:50% align:center
Come on.

00:13:31.644 --> 00:13:33.938 position:50% align:center
Momoe, don't you listen
when people talk?

00:13:34.022 --> 00:13:35.607 position:50% align:center
Wait, you mean
that crazy theory?

00:13:35.690 --> 00:13:39.152 position:50% align:center
That my uncle might have been
wrapped up in Koito's suicide?

00:13:39.235 --> 00:13:40.570 position:50% align:center
I told you, there's no way.

00:13:40.653 --> 00:13:42.364 position:50% align:center
But what if the theory's true?

00:13:42.447 --> 00:13:44.366 position:50% align:center
Mister Sawaki's
younger than Ai's mom,

00:13:44.449 --> 00:13:46.910 position:50% align:center
that means he'd be Ai's mom's
"younger live-in boy toy."

00:13:46.993 --> 00:13:48.328 position:50% align:center
Yeah, so, what?

00:13:48.411 --> 00:13:50.413 position:50% align:center
You're killing me.

00:13:50.497 --> 00:13:52.207 position:50% align:center
Look, live-in
boyfriends notoriously

00:13:52.290 --> 00:13:54.000 position:50% align:center
abuse their girlfriends' kids.

00:13:54.084 --> 00:13:55.418 position:50% align:center
It's a thing.

00:13:55.502 --> 00:13:58.171 position:50% align:center
Violently if it's a son
and sexually with a daughter.

00:13:58.254 --> 00:14:01.424 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry, but don't lump my
uncle in with creeps like that,

00:14:01.508 --> 00:14:03.593 position:50% align:center
like the men <i>your</i> mom's dated.

00:14:03.677 --> 00:14:05.095 position:50% align:center
What'd you say?

00:14:05.178 --> 00:14:06.262 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
You think it's possible

00:14:06.346 --> 00:14:08.306 position:50% align:center
that Mister Sawaki
is likes young girls,

00:14:08.390 --> 00:14:10.392 position:50% align:center
meaning that Ai's mom
is simply a decoy,

00:14:10.475 --> 00:14:12.477 position:50% align:center
and he's really after Ai.

00:14:12.560 --> 00:14:13.645 position:50% align:center
Absolutely not!

00:14:13.728 --> 00:14:14.854 position:50% align:center
He isn't like that!

00:14:14.938 --> 00:14:17.899 position:50% align:center
And plus he knows
Ai's my friend.

00:14:17.982 --> 00:14:20.276 position:50% align:center
I don't think that's it, either.

00:14:21.444 --> 00:14:22.862 position:50% align:center
I guess I...

00:14:22.946 --> 00:14:26.449 position:50% align:center
I hate not knowing
why Koito killed herself.

00:14:26.533 --> 00:14:27.909 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
If they get married one day,

00:14:27.992 --> 00:14:31.454 position:50% align:center
then you'll have to cover
for him to protect your mom.

00:14:31.538 --> 00:14:34.040 position:50% align:center
[MOMOE]
Unbelievable. I've heard enough.

00:14:34.124 --> 00:14:35.208 position:50% align:center
Wait. I'm sorry.

00:14:35.291 --> 00:14:37.335 position:50% align:center
That's not what I meant!

00:14:37.419 --> 00:14:39.879 position:50% align:center
[ACCA] What on Earth
are they talking about?

00:14:39.963 --> 00:14:41.506 position:50% align:center
[URA-ACCA]
No clue.

00:14:41.589 --> 00:14:42.716 position:50% align:center
They're definitely
not discussing

00:14:42.799 --> 00:14:44.384 position:50% align:center
how to build an outfit
around their necklaces.

00:14:44.467 --> 00:14:45.844 position:50% align:center
I can tell you that much.

00:14:45.927 --> 00:14:47.470 position:50% align:center
[ACCA]
Well, sometimes family matters

00:14:47.554 --> 00:14:50.640 position:50% align:center
take precedence over
life-or-death battles.

00:14:50.724 --> 00:14:51.850 position:50% align:center
Annoying.

00:14:51.933 --> 00:14:53.101 position:50% align:center
I guess we'll never
find out the truth

00:14:53.184 --> 00:14:54.811 position:50% align:center
about Koito unless
we bring her back

00:14:54.894 --> 00:14:56.438 position:50% align:center
and ask her ourselves.

00:14:56.521 --> 00:14:58.815 position:50% align:center
It's Occam's razor.

00:14:58.898 --> 00:15:00.442 position:50% align:center
As in there might be
a complicating factor

00:15:00.525 --> 00:15:02.152 position:50% align:center
we've yet to consider.

00:15:02.235 --> 00:15:04.654 position:50% align:center
Wait, there's more?

00:15:04.738 --> 00:15:06.740 position:50% align:center
Spill it, already!

00:15:06.823 --> 00:15:08.867 position:50% align:center
Ai likes Mister Sawaki, too.

00:15:08.950 --> 00:15:11.119 position:50% align:center
--Huh?!
--Huh?!

00:15:11.202 --> 00:15:12.537 position:50% align:center
Let's go!

00:15:12.620 --> 00:15:14.497 position:50% align:center
"The simplest theory's
usually correct."

00:15:14.581 --> 00:15:16.166 position:50% align:center
What are you
talking about, Neiru?

00:15:16.249 --> 00:15:17.834 position:50% align:center
That's not true!
You're wrong!

00:15:17.917 --> 00:15:22.005 position:50% align:center
[giggles]
Juicy! Complicated and juicy!

00:15:22.088 --> 00:15:23.381 position:50% align:center
That's not it!

00:15:23.465 --> 00:15:26.051 position:50% align:center
I don't like him even
a little bit, okay?

00:15:28.428 --> 00:15:30.597 position:50% align:center
[YAE shrieks]

00:15:30.680 --> 00:15:34.184 position:50% align:center
Stop! Please don't!

00:15:34.267 --> 00:15:36.186 position:50% align:center
Stay back!

00:15:36.269 --> 00:15:37.520 position:50% align:center
I didn't ask to
be able to see you.

00:15:37.604 --> 00:15:39.105 position:50% align:center
I just do!

00:15:39.189 --> 00:15:42.442 position:50% align:center
But that doesn't mean I'm your
friend or anything like that!

00:15:48.615 --> 00:15:50.033 position:50% align:center
No!

00:16:03.046 --> 00:16:08.343 position:50% align:center
Huh? No. Stop it!

00:16:08.426 --> 00:16:09.803 position:50% align:center
It's here?

00:16:09.886 --> 00:16:12.597 position:50% align:center
But I... can't see it.

00:16:12.681 --> 00:16:16.351 position:50% align:center
Please, don't kill that girl!

00:16:19.020 --> 00:16:20.522 position:50% align:center
Prayer beads?

00:16:22.941 --> 00:16:24.859 position:50% align:center
[MOMOE] Wait, you mean
that crazy theory?

00:16:24.943 --> 00:16:28.780 position:50% align:center
That my uncle might have been
wrapped up in Koito's suicide?

00:16:31.449 --> 00:16:35.537 position:50% align:center
We've been thinking that
we might like to start dating.

00:16:43.712 --> 00:16:45.380 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU] As in here might
be a complicating factor

00:16:45.463 --> 00:16:48.133 position:50% align:center
we've yet to consider.

00:16:48.216 --> 00:16:50.802 position:50% align:center
There's no reason for you
to have a complex about it.

00:16:50.885 --> 00:16:51.845 position:50% align:center
Your eyes are charming.

00:16:51.928 --> 00:16:53.096 position:50% align:center
Unique.

00:16:56.224 --> 00:16:58.560 position:50% align:center
[NEIRU]
Ai likes Mister Sawaki, too.

00:17:01.563 --> 00:17:02.856 position:50% align:center
[AI]
No.

00:17:05.567 --> 00:17:07.527 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I don't.

00:17:08.778 --> 00:17:10.947 position:50% align:center
No!

00:17:16.161 --> 00:17:17.954 position:50% align:center
I don't like him.

00:17:18.038 --> 00:17:19.289 position:50% align:center
Can you...

00:17:21.541 --> 00:17:25.170 position:50% align:center
I telling you. I don't!

00:17:39.517 --> 00:17:43.104 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Now, I'm really angry!

00:17:53.323 --> 00:17:57.327 position:50% align:center
So, miss, you can see me, too?

00:17:58.161 --> 00:18:00.413 position:50% align:center
But I can't be your friend.

00:18:06.127 --> 00:18:07.879 position:50% align:center
I bet it was tough,

00:18:07.962 --> 00:18:11.299 position:50% align:center
dealing with these monsters,
all on your own.

00:18:11.383 --> 00:18:14.302 position:50% align:center
Huh? You mean you believe me?

00:18:14.386 --> 00:18:16.096 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Of course.

00:18:18.098 --> 00:18:26.606 position:50% align:center
♪ march-style music playing ♪

00:18:26.690 --> 00:18:29.192 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Your name is Leon.

00:18:29.275 --> 00:18:32.904 position:50% align:center
That's lame, huh? <i>Veni.</i>

00:18:37.033 --> 00:18:38.159 position:50% align:center
[AI]
<i>Redi.</i>

00:18:42.706 --> 00:18:44.124 position:50% align:center
<i>Veni.</i>

00:18:48.795 --> 00:18:49.587 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
Hey, Ai?

00:18:49.671 --> 00:18:52.298 position:50% align:center
Mister Sawaki is leaving now.

00:18:52.382 --> 00:18:53.508 position:50% align:center
[SAWAKI]
Don't mind me.

00:18:53.591 --> 00:18:54.759 position:50% align:center
Bye, Ohto.

00:18:54.843 --> 00:18:56.803 position:50% align:center
See you next week.

00:19:13.361 --> 00:19:16.865 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
I'm home. You in the bath, Ai?

00:19:16.948 --> 00:19:18.324 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Hi, Mom.

00:19:18.408 --> 00:19:20.702 position:50% align:center
[TAE] Don't leave
your dirty clothes there.

00:19:20.785 --> 00:19:22.037 position:50% align:center
What do I always tell you?

00:19:22.120 --> 00:19:25.457 position:50% align:center
Turn the pockets inside-out
before we wash things.

00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:28.960 position:50% align:center
[TAE]
There was stuff in your pockets.

00:19:29.044 --> 00:19:30.754 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna put it right here.

00:19:33.006 --> 00:19:34.841 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:19:36.343 --> 00:19:39.429 position:50% align:center
[TAE] Hey! Ai, wait!
You'll catch cold!

00:19:39.512 --> 00:19:41.139 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I'll be fine!

00:19:41.890 --> 00:19:44.642 position:50% align:center
Where are you even
going dressed like that?

00:19:44.726 --> 00:19:45.685 position:50% align:center
To school!

00:19:45.769 --> 00:19:47.020 position:50% align:center
What?

00:20:23.431 --> 00:20:25.725 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT B]
See ya, Mister S!

00:20:25.809 --> 00:20:27.560 position:50% align:center
[SAWAKI]
Have a good one!

00:20:29.270 --> 00:20:31.064 position:50% align:center
Mister Sawaki.

00:20:44.828 --> 00:20:46.705 position:50% align:center
[SAWAKI]
Ohto?

00:20:47.747 --> 00:20:49.582 position:50% align:center
You okay?

00:20:55.922 --> 00:20:59.300 position:50% align:center
Ohto, look. The sky.

00:20:59.384 --> 00:21:01.678 position:50% align:center
It's so clear and beautiful.

00:21:01.761 --> 00:21:03.722 position:50% align:center
It was just a passing shower.

00:21:06.057 --> 00:21:07.434 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I--!

00:21:13.481 --> 00:21:15.275 position:50% align:center
I'm...

00:21:18.903 --> 00:21:20.905 position:50% align:center
I'm coming back to school!

00:22:58.378 --> 00:22:59.671 position:50% align:center
[AI]
To be continued.